      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/11/2",
      "text": [
        " :\nسَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ عَلَيْهِ كُرٌّ مِنْ طَعَامٍ فَاشْتَرَى كُرّاً مِنْ رَجُلٍ فَقَالَ لِلرَّجُلِ اِنْطَلِقْ فَاسْتَوْفِ حَقَّكَ قَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3773 - Abd Al-Rahman ibn Abi Abdillah narrated from Abu Abdillah (as):\nI asked him about a man who owed a kurr (a measure) of food and then purchased a kurr from another man. He said to the seller, \"Go and take your right (measure) from the food I owe.\"\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in that.\""
        ]
      }
    },
